- IP addresses = Internet Protocol
- IPv4 address = 32 bits
- 2 devices on the Internet can't have the same address at the same time
- address space of IPv4 = 2^32 = > 4 billion

2 Notations for IPv4 addresses:
- binary 
- dotted decimal

Valid IP addreses:
- 4 octets
- each octet has a value from 0-255

